msgid "wizardContent.assign.purpose"
msgstr "Each completed course must sit under a requirement it satisfies. Unassigned courses block schedule generation until they are placed."

msgid "wizardContent.assign.title"
msgstr "Fill requirements"

msgid "wizardContent.assign.whatToDo"
msgstr "Assign every completed course to the requirement node it fulfills. Continue until the planner reports that all courses are assigned."

msgid "wizardContent.completed.purpose"
msgstr "The planner subtracts what you have already done from your requirements and uses this list when assigning courses to requirement slots."

msgid "wizardContent.completed.title"
msgstr "Add completed courses"

msgid "wizardContent.completed.whatToDo"
msgstr "Add every course you have completed or are currently taking, using course codes. You can refine this list after a transcript upload from the Program step."

msgid "wizardContent.generate.purpose"
msgstr "The solver builds conflict-free timetables from your selections using your preferences for load, times, and days."

msgid "wizardContent.generate.title"
msgstr "Generate schedules"

msgid "wizardContent.generate.whatToDo"
msgstr "Set how many courses you want this term, earliest start and latest end times, allowed days, and optional minimum professor rating. Adjust first-year credit cap or compressed schedule if shown, then click Generate Schedules."

msgid "wizardContent.mode.purpose"
msgstr "UOPlan supports two modes. Basic mode lets you quickly select required courses and electives without full program planning. Advanced mode builds your entire degree structure."

msgid "wizardContent.mode.title"
msgstr "Choose mode"

msgid "wizardContent.mode.whatToDo"
msgstr "Select either Basic mode for quick scheduling, or Advanced mode for comprehensive degree planning."

msgid "wizardContent.options.purpose"
msgstr "Some programs include branches, majors, or option groups. This step records which path you are following so the correct requirement subtree is used."

msgid "wizardContent.options.title"
msgstr "Choose path"

msgid "wizardContent.options.whatToDo"
msgstr "Work through each choice in order. Pick one option where required; use the back control inside a drilldown if you need to change a branch."

msgid "wizardContent.program.purpose"
msgstr "Your program and starting year determine which degree requirements apply. Discipline lists help evaluate program-specific prerequisites."

msgid "wizardContent.program.title"
msgstr "Select program"

msgid "wizardContent.program.whatToDo"
msgstr "Set your first year of study, then search and select your program. Optionally upload an unofficial transcript PDF to auto-detect year, program, and completed courses - processing stays entirely on your device."

msgid "wizardContent.share.purpose"
msgstr "A shareable link encodes your term, program, completed courses, and planner selections so you can revisit or send your plan to someone else."

msgid "wizardContent.share.title"
msgstr "Share"

msgid "wizardContent.share.whatToDo"
msgstr "Click Share in the header to copy the URL to your clipboard. After you generate timetables, you can also share from the calendar view."

msgid "wizardContent.term.purpose"
msgstr "Schedule data and section offerings are tied to a specific academic term. Choosing the right term ensures the planner uses courses that are actually offered when you plan to study."

msgid "wizardContent.term.title"
msgstr "Choose term"

msgid "wizardContent.term.whatToDo"
msgstr "Select the term you are planning for from the list. You must have a term selected before you can generate schedules."

msgid "wizardContent.tour.whatFor"
msgstr "What this step is for"

msgid "wizardContent.tour.whatToDo"
msgstr "What you should do"

